{
  "text": "In systems theory, reduced order modeling has also been extensively studied under the name of model reduction [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] . Contrary to model reduction where approximation is measured using L 2 norms we are interested in L \u221e norms. The guarantees provided by L \u221e norms are more natural when applications to safety verification are of interest.",
  "citation_candidates": [
